Package: EconGeo
Title: Computing Key Indicators of the Spatial Distribution of Economic
    Activities
Version: 1.1
Author: Pierre-Alexandre Balland <p.balland@uu.nl>
Maintainer: Pierre-Alexandre Balland <p.balland@uu.nl>
Description: Functions to compute a series of indices commonly used to describe
    the location, distribution, spatial organization, and complexity of economic
    activities. Most of the function uses matrix calculus and use bipartite
    (incidence) matrices consisting of region - industry pairs.
URL: https://github.com/PABalland/EconGeo
Depends:
    R (>= 3.3.0)
Imports:
    reshape2,
    Matrix
License: GPL-2 | GPL-3 [expanded from: GPL]
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 5.0.1.9000
BugReports: http://github.com/PABalland/EconGeo/issues
